      <highlights>Gradual increase in danger of dry avalanches as a consequence of the strong wind.</highlights>
      <comment>As a consequence of sharply falling temperatures and the strong to storm force northwesterly wind, a treacherous avalanche situation will develop. &lt;br/> Wednesday: The prevalence of avalanche prone locations and likelihood of triggering will increase during the course of the night. &lt;br/> These conditions will bring about a rise in the danger of dry avalanches. Also at a distance from ridgelines medium-sized and, in isolated cases, large dry slab avalanches are possible. &lt;br/> Especially wind-loaded slopes: The fresh snow as well as all the wind slabs can be released by a single winter sport participant. &lt;br/> Backcountry touring calls for caution and restraint.</comment>
